d rusty weaps as well. Its a pain having to wait till you are massively overloaded and then run back to sell, but its what I used to do. Plus because there are tons of skellies round there you can fill up on Bones as well <img src=icon_smile.gif border=0 align=middle></P><P>You havent specified what server you are on. If you are on Karana I would give you the cash happily, 10-20pp or so is not a lot for me. Your other option is to try and ask a higher level necro for the cash.</P><P>If I get a tell along the lines of "U R a Hi lvl, gimmee pp plz" I will ignore it. <BR>If I get a tell along the lines of "Greetings Eldar Sister, I am a young and struggling Necromancer of the 9th circle who does not have the platinum to purchase his level 8 spells and is missing a lot of his level 4 spells. Would it be possible for a senior Necromancer such as yourself to help this young one?. I would probably help out someone from a tell like that. I think most senior Necros probably would as well.</P><P>Its amusing and is a little less like the usual daily begging /tells I get. I know beggars suck but its an option and you could always promise to pay the money back when you get some spare.</P><P>56 DE Necromancer<BR><br><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=49001" target="_blank">Profile</a><BR><a href="http://sizzlesites.com/Ulaa/" target="_blank">Ulaa's web site</a><br><BR><img src="http://www.sizzlesites.com/Ulaa/sig.jpg" border=0></font></td>
